p 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/cfd37/2023-heli-model2.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/cfd37/2023-heli-model1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/cfd37/2023-heli-model1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/cfd37/2023-heli-model1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/cfd37/2023-heli-model1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> </swiper-container> <p>These are sample images I rendered for the CFD37 competition, but not submitted. The visualizations highlighting key aspects such as blade vortex interactions (BVI) structures, modeling techniques and the effectiveness of advanced flow simulation methods.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="helicopter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Visualization Entries for CFD37 Competition]]></summary></entry></feed>